(thirdQuint)A Prospective Cohort of Displaced Adolescent Midshaft Clavicle Fractures.

 The study is a prospective observational cohort design of the natural history of adolescent clavicle fractures treated at the McGill University Health Centre.

 Surgeon choice will dictate treatment.

 There is no difference from the current normal therapy choice of each individual surgeon.

 Patients will be offered either operative or conservative management.

 Operative Treatment: Patients with displaced midshaft clavicle fractures will be offered operative treatment which involves open reduction and internal fixation with a plate.

 This is the standard treatment for completely displaced fractures in the adult population at our Institution based on Level 1 evidence.

 Conservative care: Patients will be treated in a sling for the acute phase of two weeks with progressive physiotherapy.

