Outcomes for displaced midshaft clavicle fractures in adolescents are not defined.

 The current method of treatment for these fractures is non-operative management.

 There is recent Level 1 evidence in the adult literature to suggest that outcomes are superior when these fractures are managed surgically with open reduction and internal fixation.

